---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>

<Fragment slot="head-scripts">
  {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}
</Fragment>

<CommercialHero
  eyebrow="Hobart FT-900 · FT-1000 · FT-1500 · Insinger · Stero Institutional"
  title="Flight Type Dishwasher Repair Los Angeles"
  subtitle="Institutional flight type dishwashers for hospitals, universities, large cafeterias. $120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Same-day across LA, OC, Ventura."
  heroImageTitle="Flight Type Dishwasher Repair"
  showBranches={true}
/>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · What we service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Flight type institutional dishwashers, 1,000+ pieces an hour.</h2>

    <p>Flight type dishwashers are the institutional scale of commercial dishwashing. Continuous flight of pegs (no racks) carries individual plates, trays, and serving pieces through pre-wash, wash, rinse, and final-rinse zones. Throughput 1,000+ pieces per hour. Massive footprint. Complex water and steam systems. Hospital cafeterias, university dining halls, large catering operations, school districts.</p>

    <p>The <strong>Hobart FT line</strong> (ITW Food Equipment Group) dominates LA institutional installs. FT-900 for smaller institutional kitchens, FT-1000 mid-size hospital cafeterias, FT-1500 for major hospital systems and university dining. Insinger and Stero appear on older installs. We service all of them.</p>

    <p>This is not a rack conveyor restaurant unit (200 to 400 racks/hour, completely different drive system). See <a href="/commercial/dishwasher-repair/rack-conveyor-dishwasher-repair/">rack conveyor dishwasher repair</a> for that scope.</p>

    <p>BHGS #A49573. EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410. BBB Accredited. Phones answered 24/7. $120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair, no emergency surcharge.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Typical flight type failures</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Flight type breaks differently than rack conveyor.</h2>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Pre-rinse spray nozzle scale.</strong> Hard SoCal water scales the high-pressure pre-rinse manifold first. Spray pattern degrades, food residue carries into wash tank. Descale plus inspect, sometimes nozzle replacement. $360 to $580.</li>
      <li><strong>Wash tank heater (electric or steam-injected).</strong> Wash tank holds 150 to 160°F. Heavier load than rack conveyor wash tank. Electric element burnout or steam coil scaled. Electric element $700 to $1,200, steam coil descale plus repair $900 to $1,600.</li>
      <li><strong>Conveyor motor and drive.</strong> Heavier sustained load than rack conveyor (continuous 1,000+ piece flow). Gearmotor wear at year 6 to 9 typical. Replacement $880 to $1,400.</li>
      <li><strong>Scrap collector and pre-wash drain.</strong> Food scraps accumulate in collector tray, drain backs up. Cleaning is routine. Scrap collector mechanism replacement $480 to $780.</li>
      <li><strong>Final-rinse booster heater.</strong> NSF 180°F compliance. Same failure mode as rack conveyor but larger element. $1,100 to $1,800.</li>
      <li><strong>Multi-zone door switches.</strong> Flight type has door interlocks at multiple points across the flight. Worn switches cascade error codes. $200 to $340 per switch, often replaced as a chain.</li>
      <li><strong>Drain solenoid and waste pump.</strong> Larger drain volume than rack conveyor, faster wear. $380 to $620.</li>
      <li><strong>Final-rinse manifold mineral scale.</strong> Same chemistry as pre-rinse but with higher temp accelerating scale formation. Descale plus jet inspection. $400 to $620.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Recent jobs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Real repair stories from the last few weeks.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Composite examples; model numbers, ages, and prices are accurate to typical scope.</p>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Pasadena · Hobart FT-1500 hospital cafeteria, 12 years old</h3>
      <p>Wash tank temperature dropping below 150°F mid-shift, sanitizing failure logged on HACCP record. Diagnosed: electric tank heater element open-circuit (24kW unit). Replaced element, descaled tank, retested at 158°F sustained. Total: $120 plus $1,180 part plus 3 hours = $1,800. HACCP corrective-action documentation provided.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Los Angeles · Hobart FT-1000 university dining, 9 years old</h3>
      <p>Conveyor stuttering then stopping mid-shift. Diagnosed: gearmotor seized at the drive sprocket, year 9 typical. Replaced gearmotor, lubricated drive, tested 30-minute continuous flight. Total: $120 plus $1,040 part plus 2.5 hours = $1,400.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Long Beach · Hobart FT-900 large catering operation, 7 years old</h3>
      <p>Multi-issue: door zone switch intermittent (cascading error codes), scrap collector drainage slow. Replaced two door switches, cleaned and rebuilt scrap collector mechanism. Total: $120 plus $560 parts plus 2.5 hours = $980.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Beverly Hills · Hobart FT-1500 luxury hotel banquet kitchen, 14 years old</h3>
      <p>Final rinse at 167°F, NSF needs 180°F. Booster heater element scaled and partially open. Replaced booster element, descaled rinse manifold, verified at 184°F. HACCP documentation. Total: $120 plus $1,420 part plus 3 hours = $2,200.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Burbank · Hobart FT-1000 school district central kitchen, 11 years old</h3>
      <p>Pre-rinse coverage uneven, food residue carrying through. Descaled pre-rinse manifold, replaced two corroded nozzles, verified spray pattern. Total: $120 plus $260 nozzles plus 2 hours = $580.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04 · Honest scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we do for flight type, and what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong> Hobart FT-900, FT-1000, FT-1500 plus Insinger and Stero institutional flight type. Electric and steam-injected tank configurations. Pre-rinse, wash, rinse, and final-rinse zones. Conveyor drive, scrap collector, multi-zone interlocks, NSF 180°F compliance verification, HACCP corrective-action documentation.</p>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> new flight type installation (specialty installer trade through manufacturer); upstream steam supply line work (steam plumbing trade); chemical supply contracts (Ecolab, Auto-Chlor, Diversey); ventilation hood work above the dishwasher (see <a href="/commercial/exhaust-hood-repair/">exhaust hood repair</a>).</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05 · Pricing</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What flight type repair actually costs.</h2>

    <table class="price-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Repair</th><th>Typical cost</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Diagnostic</td><td>$120, waived with repair</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Pre-rinse manifold descale + nozzle inspection</td><td>$360 to $580</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Wash tank electric heater element</td><td>$1,100 to $1,800</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Wash tank steam coil descale</td><td>$900 to $1,600</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Conveyor gearmotor</td><td>$1,200 to $1,800</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Scrap collector mechanism</td><td>$480 to $780</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Final-rinse booster heater element</td><td>$1,400 to $2,200</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Multi-zone door switch (per switch)</td><td>$200 to $340</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Drain solenoid / waste pump</td><td>$380 to $620</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Multi-component repair (10+ year unit)</td><td>$1,800 to $3,000</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Warranty</td><td>90 days parts and labor</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p class="price-note">$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. No emergency surcharge. We provide HACCP corrective-action documentation post-repair for institutional compliance records.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">06 · Brands we service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Hobart FT dominates institutional installs.</h2>

    <p><strong>Hobart</strong> (ITW Food Equipment Group): FT-900, FT-1000, FT-1500. The institutional standard. We carry common parts. See <a href="/brands/hobart-dishwasher-repair/">Hobart commercial dishwasher repair</a>.</p>

    <p>Insinger and Stero appear on older institutional installs (pre-2015 typically). Still serviceable, parts available through manufacturer distribution networks with 5 to 10 day lead time.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">07 · Why operators call us</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Eight reasons.</h2>

    <ul class="why-list">
      <li><strong>Hobart FT specialization.</strong> Most appliance shops decline flight type because of size and complexity. We do them.</li>
      <li><strong>HACCP corrective-action documentation.</strong> Post-repair documentation for hospital and school district records.</li>
      <li><strong>NSF 180°F final rinse verification.</strong> We measure at the manifold during a live cycle, document for health authority.</li>
      <li><strong>Steam-injected tank service.</strong> Steam coil descale and steam control valve service. Many shops decline steam-side work.</li>
      <li><strong>BHGS #A49573 plus EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410.</strong> Verifiable.</li>
      <li><strong>24/7 phone answering, no emergency surcharge.</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Same-day across LA, OC, Ventura.</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Honest scope.</strong> Steam supply line and chemical supply contracts get referred. We service the dishwasher itself.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Sister sub-services: <a href="/commercial/dishwasher-repair/rack-conveyor-dishwasher-repair/">rack conveyor</a>, <a href="/commercial/dishwasher-repair/undercounter-dishwasher-repair/">undercounter</a>, <a href="/commercial/dishwasher-repair/glass-washer-repair/">glass washer</a>. Parent: <a href="/commercial/dishwasher-repair/">commercial dishwasher repair</a>. Credentials: <a href="/credentials/licensed/">BHGS license</a>, <a href="/credentials/epa-certified/">EPA 608</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">08 · FAQ</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Flight type dishwasher repair, common questions.</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      {faqs.map((f) => (
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>{f.q}</summary>
          <p>{f.a}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="bottom-cta">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Flight Type Down? Call Us 24/7.</h2>
    <p>Hobart FT specialists. $120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Same-day across LA, OC, Ventura. No emergency surcharge. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410.</p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a href={phoneHref} class="btn-primary">☎ Call {phone}</a>
      <a href="/contact/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
